37._UX200_CR0,39,200,200_.jpg"/></a></div><div class="AuthorPreview__info"><h3 class="Text H3"><a class="ContributorLink" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/6237.Charles_Lamb"><span class="ContributorLink__name" data-testid="name">Charles Lamb</span></a></h3><div class="AuthorPreview__meta"><span class="Text Text__body3 Text__subdued">387<!-- --> <!-- -->books<span class="u-dot-before">147<!-- --> <!-- -->followers</span></span></div></div></div><div class="TruncatedText"><div class="TruncatedText__text TruncatedText__text--3" data-testid="contentContainer"><div><span class="Formatted">Charles Lamb was an English essayist with Welsh heritage, best known for his "Essays of Elia" and for the children's book "Tales from Shakespeare", which he produced along with his sister, <b>
